  <HelpTexts>
    <string><![CDATA[Welcome to the battlefield, Commander.


To skip this short tutorial, press [Cancel]. You can always checks the help on the main menu for a quick reminder.


[Continue]]]></string>
    <string>
      <![CDATA[Your mission is simple, Commander: do not let asteroids reach the end of the path.


You see the planet with 5 pink moons? It means a maximum of 5 asteroids can reach it before you loose. To avoid this, we're going to build turrets. Lot of them.


[Continue]]]>
    </string>
    <string>
      <![CDATA[But before we talk about turrets, look at the sandglass at the top-right of the screen. When the sandglass is depleted, a wave of asteroids will start. The numbers means, in order: the number of waves remaining (5), the amount of cash you have to buy turrets (1000M$) and your score (0!).


[Continue]]]>
    </string>
    <string>
      <![CDATA[Here an important tip: you can click on the sandglass to make the next wave start faster!


Now the fun part: your main job is to build and upgrade turrets. These two actions cost money and you gain money by killing asteroids. You can buy a turret on a planet.


[Continue]]]>
    </string>
    <string>
      <![CDATA[You can only place turrets around planets. Upgrading turrets make them stronger in various ways (range, fire rate, etc). To upgrade a turret, you put your cursor on it and choose the green option.


[Continue]]]>
    </string>
    <string>
      <![CDATA[Here's another important tip: Maintain [AdvancedView] to see the range of your turrets (and more!).


This is it for now, Commander. You'll receive further instructions in other levels. Oh, one last thing: you better save this system, otherwise you're fired! Good luck.


[Continue]]]>
    </string>
